The clan is also associated with the use of "Tachibana" (橘) and the mythical rejuvenating "Ochimizu" (変若水). Several descendants later adopted the {{ill|Tachibana no Ason|ja|橘朝臣}} surname.<ref>Toshio Hōga, "[http://wwr2.ucom.ne.jp/hetoyc15/keihu/monobekz/monobek1.htm Examination of the Mononobe Lineage in the ''Tenson Hongi'']," ''Kojiki no Homma,'' 2008.</ref>

== Headquarters ==
=== Main Base ===
The headquarters of the Tōtsuōmi Kokuzō were in {{ill|Iwata District, Tōtōmi|ja|磐田郡}}, corresponding to modern {{ill|Iwata, Shizuoka|ja|磐田市}}. This area later became the site of the provincial {{ill|kokufu|ja|国府}} and {{ill|Provincial temple|ja|国分寺}} of Tōtōmi Province.

=== Territory ===
The Tōtsuōmi Kokuzō governed the region known as Tōtsuōmi, later divided into Iwata District and surrounding areas, including {{ill|Yamakō District, Tōtōmi|ja|山香郡}}, {{ill|Nagakami District, Tōtōmi|ja|長上郡}}, and {{ill|Nagashimo District, Tōtōmi|ja|長下郡}}.

The boundaries of the Kokuzō's territory remain debated, with theories including:
* Surroundings of {{ill|Lake Hamana|ja|浜名湖}}.
* West of the {{ill|Tenryū River|ja|天竜川}}.
* From Lake Hamana to the western edge of {{ill|Iwata Plain|ja|磐田原}}.
* From Lake Hamana to the {{ill|Ōtagawa River|ja|太田川}} basin.

== Clan Deity ==
=== Shrine Associations ===
* '''{{ill|Ōmi Kunitama Shrine|ja|淡海國玉神社}}'''
: Located in {{ill|Mitsuke, Iwata|ja|磐田市見付}}, this shrine is the {{ill|sōja|ja|惣社}} of Tōtōmi Province and enshrines {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主神}}.

* '''{{ill|Oguni Shrine|ja|小国神社}}'''
: Located in {{ill|Mori, Shizuoka|ja|森町}}, this shrine is the {{ill|Ichinomiya|ja|一宮}} of Tōtōmi Province, enshrining {{ill|Ōnamuchi no Mikoto|ja|大己貴神}}.

