The clan belonged to the {{ill|Mononobe clan|ja|物部氏|12=draft|12=draft}}. While the clan's official {{ill|uji|ja|氏|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|kabane|ja|姓|12=draft|12=draft}} remain uncertain, it is believed to have adopted '''Tōtsuōmi''' (遠淡海氏) as its name, with the kabane of '''Nao''' (直), like its related clans {{ill|Kuno clan|ja|久努氏|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Saya clan|ja|佐夜氏|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref>"[http://wwr2.ucom.ne.jp/hetoyc15/keihu/sizokugairan/mononobe2g.htm Overview of the Mononobe Clan]," ''Kojiki no Homma,'' 2003.</ref>

The clan is also associated with the use of "Tachibana" (橘) and the mythical rejuvenating "Ochimizu" (変若水). Several descendants later adopted the {{ill|Tachibana no Ason|ja|橘朝臣|12=draft|12=draft}} surname.<ref>Toshio Hōga, "[http://wwr2.ucom.ne.jp/hetoyc15/keihu/monobekz/monobek1.htm Examination of the Mononobe Lineage in the ''Tenson Hongi'']," ''Kojiki no Homma,'' 2008.</ref>

== Headquarters ==
=== Main Base ===
The headquarters of the Tōtsuōmi Kokuzō were in {{ill|Iwata District, Tōtōmi|ja|磐田郡|12=draft|12=draft}}, corresponding to modern {{ill|Iwata, Shizuoka|ja|磐田市|12=draft|12=draft}}. This area later became the site of the provincial {{ill|kokufu|ja|国府|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Provincial temple|ja|国分寺|12=draft|12=draft}} of Tōtōmi Province.

=== Territory ===
The Tōtsuōmi Kokuzō governed the region known as Tōtsuōmi, later divided into Iwata District and surrounding areas, including {{ill|Yamakō District, Tōtōmi|ja|山香郡|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Nagakami District, Tōtōmi|ja|長上郡|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Nagashimo District, Tōtōmi|ja|長下郡|12=draft|12=draft}}.

The boundaries of the Kokuzō's territory remain debated, with theories including:
* Surroundings of {{ill|Lake Hamana|ja|浜名湖|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* West of the {{ill|Tenryū River|ja|天竜川|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* From Lake Hamana to the western edge of {{ill|Iwata Plain|ja|磐田原|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* From Lake Hamana to the {{ill|Ōtagawa River|ja|太田川|12=draft|12=draft}} basin.

