'''Tōtsuōmi Kokuzō''' (遠淡海国造) refers to the {{ill|Kokuzō|ja|国造|12=draft|12=draft}} of Tōtsuōmi Province, which encompassed the western region of {{ill|Tōtōmi Province|ja|遠江国|12=draft|12=draft}}. The title is also rendered as Tōtōmi Kokuzō.

== Overview ==

* The {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|12=draft|12=draft}} mentions the title as '''Tōtōmi Kokuzō'''. The {{ill|Sendai Kuji Hongi|ja|先代旧事本紀|12=draft|12=draft}} refers to it as '''Tōtsuōmi Kokuzō'''. The progenitor of the Tōtsuōmi Kokuzō is recorded as {{ill|Takehi-Nateru|ja|建比良鳥命|1=Takehi-Nateru|Takehi-Nateru=Takehi-Nateru|lt=Takeruhiratori no Mikoto|12=draft|12=draft}}, a descendant of [[Ame no Hohi]], linking the lineage to the {{ill|Izumo clan|ja|Izumo Province 造|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Musashi no Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|武蔵国造|lt=Musashi Kokuzō|12=draft|12=draft}}, and other related clans.
* The ''Kokuzō Hongi'' of the ''Sendai Kuji Hongi'' names {{ill|Inagimi no Mikoto|ja|印岐美命|12=draft|12=draft}}, a descendant of {{ill|Ikagashiko-o|ja|伊香色雄命|12=draft|12=draft}}, as the Kokuzō during the reign of {{ill|Emperor Seimu|ja|成務天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* The ''Tenson Hongi'' states that Inagimi no Mikoto, the brother of {{ill|Katakatane no Mikoto|ja|片堅石命|12=draft|12=draft}}, founder of {{ill|Suruga Kokuzō|ja|珠流河国造|12=draft|12=draft}}, was appointed Kokuzō of Tōtsuōmi. This record also describes Inagimi as the ancestor of {{ill|Shiki Agatanushi|ja|志紀県主|12=draft|12=draft}}, Tōtsuōmi Kokuzō, and several related clans.<ref name="takao">Toshio Hōga, "[http://wwr2.ucom.ne.jp/hetoyc15/hitori/takaosan1.htm Preservation Issues of Takao-san Kofun]," ''Kojiki no Homma,'' 2015.</ref>

