}}

'''Tōtsuōmi Kokuzō''' (遠淡海国造) refers to the {{ill|Kokuzō|ja|国造|qq=draft|qq=draft}} of Tōtsuōmi Province, which encompassed the western region of {{ill|Tōtōmi Province|ja|遠江国|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The title is also rendered as Tōtōmi Kokuzō.

== Overview ==

* The {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|qq=draft|qq=draft}} mentions the title as '''Tōtōmi Kokuzō'''. The {{ill|Sendai Kuji Hongi|ja|先代旧事本紀|qq=draft|qq=draft}} refers to it as '''Tōtsuōmi Kokuzō'''. The progenitor of the Tōtsuōmi Kokuzō is recorded as {{ill|Takehi-Nateru|ja|建比良鳥命|1=Takehi-Nateru|Takehi-Nateru=Takehi-Nateru|lt=Takeruhiratori no Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a descendant of [[Ame no Hohi]], linking the lineage to the {{ill|Izumo clan|ja|Izumo Province 造|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Musashi no Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|武蔵国造|lt=Musashi Kokuzō|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and other related clans.
* The ''Kokuzō Hongi'' of the ''Sendai Kuji Hongi'' names {{ill|Inagimi no Mikoto|ja|印岐美命|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a descendant of {{ill|Ikagashiko-o|ja|伊香色雄|1=Ikagashiko-o命|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, as the Kokuzō during the reign of {{ill|Emperor Seimu|ja|成務天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
* The ''Tenson Hongi'' states that Inagimi no Mikoto, the brother of {{ill|Katakatane no Mikoto|ja|片堅石命|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, founder of {{ill|Suruga Kokuzō|ja|珠流河国造|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, was appointed Kokuzō of Tōtsuōmi. This record also describes Inagimi as the ancestor of {{ill|Shiki Agatanushi|ja|志紀県主|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Tōtsuōmi Kokuzō, and several related clans.<ref name="takao">Toshio Hōga, "[http://wwr2.ucom.ne.jp/hetoyc15/hitori/takaosan1.htm Preservation Issues of Takao-san Kofun]," ''Kojiki no Homma,'' 2015.</ref>

=== Clan ===
The clan belonged to the {{ill|Mononobe clan|ja|物部氏|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. While the clan's official {{ill|uji|ja|氏|1=Uji (clan)|lt=Uji|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|kabane|ja|姓|qq=draft|qq=draft}} remain uncertain, it is believed to have adopted '''Tōtsuōmi''' (遠淡海氏) as its name, with the kabane of '''Nao''' (直), like its related clans {{ill|Kuno clan|ja|久努氏|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Saya clan|ja|佐夜氏|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref>"[http://wwr2.ucom.ne.jp/hetoyc15/keihu/sizokugairan/mononobe2g.htm Overview of the Mononobe Clan]," ''Kojiki no Homma,'' 2003.</ref>

The clan is also associated with the use of "Tachibana" (橘) and the mythical rejuvenating "Ochimizu" (変若水). Several descendants later adopted the {{ill|Tachibana no Ason|ja|橘朝臣|qq=draft|qq=draft}} surname.<ref>Toshio Hōga, "[http://wwr2.ucom.ne.jp/hetoyc15/keihu/monobekz/monobek1.htm Examination of the Mononobe Lineage in the ''Tenson Hongi'']," ''Kojiki no Homma,'' 2008.</ref>

== Headquarters ==
=== Main Base ===
The headquarters of the Tōtsuōmi Kokuzō were in {{ill|Iwata District, Tōtōmi|ja|磐田郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, corresponding to modern {{ill|Iwata, Shizuoka|ja|磐田市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. This area later became the site of the provincial {{ill|kokufu|ja|国府|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Provincial temple|ja|国分寺|qq=draft|qq=draft}} of Tōtōmi Province.

=== Territory ===
The Tōtsuōmi Kokuzō governed the region known as Tōtsuōmi, later divided into Iwata District and surrounding areas, including {{ill|Yamakō District, Tōtōmi|ja|山香郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Nagakami District, Tōtōmi|ja|長上郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Nagashimo District, Tōtōmi|ja|長下郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

The boundaries of the Kokuzō's territory remain debated, with theories including:
* Surroundings of {{ill|Lake Hamana|ja|浜名湖|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
* West of the {{ill|Tenryū River|ja|天竜川|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
* From Lake Hamana to the western edge of {{ill|Iwata Plain|ja|磐田原|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
* From Lake Hamana to the {{ill|Ōtagawa River|ja|太田川|qq=draft|qq=draft}} basin.

== Clan Deity ==
=== Shrine Associations ===
* '''{{ill|Ōmi Kunitama Shrine|ja|淡海國玉神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'''
: Located in {{ill|Mitsuke, Iwata|ja|磐田市見付|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, this shrine is the {{ill|sōja|ja|惣社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} of Tōtōmi Province and enshrines {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

* '''{{ill|Oguni Shrine|ja|小国神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'''
: Located in {{ill|Mori, Shizuoka|ja|森町|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, this shrine is the {{ill|Ichinomiya|ja|一宮|1=Ichinomiya|qq=draft|qq=draft}} of Tōtōmi Province, enshrining {{ill|Ōnamuchi no Mikoto|ja|大己貴神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

=== Burial Sites ===
* '''{{ill|Teradani Chōshizuka Kofun|lt=Kochōshizuka Kofun|ja|小銚子塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'''

